# ~/.ssh/hosts.local
#
# PURPOSE
# -------
# Local SSH host definitions.
#
# This file is intentionally not committed.
#
# Use this file for personal, environment-specific, or sensitive SSH hosts.
# It is included from ~/.ssh/config.
#
# CHEZMOI WORKFLOW
# ----------------
# This file uses chezmoi's native `create_` prefix, which means:
# - It will be created on first apply if it doesn't exist
# - Once created, it will never be overwritten by chezmoi
# - You can edit ~/.ssh/hosts.local directly and your changes are safe
#
# The `create_` prefix is the native chezmoi way to handle "apply once" files.
# No manual ignore list management needed!
#
# Start by uncommenting and customising entries as needed.

